# AWS Application Load Balancer (ALB) Lab

## Path-Based Routing and Normal Routing

---

## 📌 Lab Objective

In this lab, students will learn how to:

* Launch EC2 instances
* Install and configure a web server
* Create Target Groups
* Create an Application Load Balancer (ALB)
* Configure **Normal Routing**
* Configure **Path-Based Routing**
* Test the load balancer using URL paths

---

## 🏗 Architecture

```
                Internet Users
                       |
                       |
           Application Load Balancer
                       |
        ---------------------------------
        |                               |
     /app1                           /app2
        |                               |
    EC2 Instance 1                EC2 Instance 2
     (APP1 Server)                (APP2 Server)
```

---

# 📋 Prerequisites

Before starting this lab, make sure you have:

* AWS Account
* Basic knowledge of AWS EC2
* Key Pair for EC2 access
* Security Group allowing **HTTP (Port 80)**

---

# 🚀 Step 1: Launch EC2 Instance 1

Go to:

```
AWS Console → EC2 → Launch Instance
```

### Instance Configuration

| Setting        | Value           |
| -------------- | --------------- |
| Name           | App1-Server     |
| AMI            | Amazon Linux 2  |
| Instance Type  | t2.micro        |
| Security Group | Allow HTTP (80) |
| Key Pair       | Your key pair   |

### User Data Script

Paste the following script:

```bash
#!/bin/bash
yum update -y
yum install -y httpd
systemctl start httpd
systemctl enable httpd
echo "<h1>Welcome to APP1 Server</h1>" > /var/www/html/index.html
```

Launch the instance.

---

# 🚀 Step 2: Launch EC2 Instance 2

Repeat the same process.

### Instance Configuration

| Setting       | Value          |
| ------------- | -------------- |
| Name          | App2-Server    |
| AMI           | Amazon Linux 2 |
| Instance Type | t2.micro       |

### User Data Script

```bash
#!/bin/bash
