# 🎯 Step 3: Create Target Groups

Go to:

```
EC2 → Target Groups → Create Target Group
```

---

## Target Group 1

| Setting     | Value       |
| ----------- | ----------- |
| Target Type | Instances   |
| Name        | app1-target |
| Protocol    | HTTP        |
| Port        | 80          |

Register target:

```
App1-Server
```

---

## Target Group 2

| Setting     | Value       |
| ----------- | ----------- |
| Target Type | Instances   |
| Name        | app2-target |
| Protocol    | HTTP        |
| Port        | 80          |

Register target:

```
App2-Server
```

---

# ⚖ Step 4: Create Application Load Balancer

Go to:

```
EC2 → Load Balancers → Create Load Balancer
```

Select:

```
Application Load Balancer
```

---

## Load Balancer Configuration

| Setting            | Value             |
| ------------------ | ----------------- |
| Name               | My-Application-LB |
| Scheme             | Internet-facing   |
| Listener           | HTTP (80)         |
| Availability Zones | Select 2 subnets  |

Security Group:

Allow **HTTP (Port 80)**

Default Target Group:

```
app1-target
```

Click **Create Load Balancer**

---

# 🔀 Step 5: Configure Path-Based Routing

Go to:

```
EC2 → Load Balancers → My-Application-LB
```

Open:

```
Listeners → View/Edit Rules
```

---

## Rule 1

Condition

```
Path is /app1*
```

Action

```
Forward to app1-target
```

---

## Rule 2

Condition

```
Path is /app2*
```

Action

```
Forward to app2-target
```

Save the rules.

---

# 🧪 Step 6: Testing the Load Balancer

Copy the **Load Balancer DNS Name**

Example:

```
http://my-alb-123456.us-east-1.elb.amazonaws.com
```

---

## Test Default Routing

```
http://ALB-DNS
```

Expected Output:

```
Welcome to APP1 Server
```

---

## Test APP1 Routing

```
http://ALB-DNS/app1
```

Expected Output:

```
Welcome to APP1 Server
```

---

## Test APP2 Routing

```
http://ALB-DNS/app2
```

Expected Output:

```
Welcome to APP2 Server
```

---

# ✅ Expected Result

| URL     | Output      |
| ------- | ----------- |
| ALB DNS | APP1 Server |
| /app1   | APP1 Server |
| /app2   | APP2 Server |

